Hi! I'm Jacqueline Zamitalo.

I am a second-year Computer Science major and International Engineering minor in the Burnett Honors College at the University of Central Florida. I love programming and welcome every chance to practice and learn the concepts, languages, and skills behind software engineering.

While at UCF, I have served as an Undergraduate Teaching Assistant in Concepts in Computer Science and Computer Science 1, two of the foundational CS courses at UCF. In these roles, I've used my knowledge of Python and C to assist students in their CS journeys. Additionally, I've spent a semester interning at a local non-profit, where I worked on the Computer Programming team and contributed to the company's development of prosthetic limbs for children in the limb-difference community. I am also a member of multiple student organizations at UCF, including the Society of Women Engineers, KnightHacks, and the Google Student Developer Club.

Outside of school, I enjoy reading, writing, watching movies, playing sports, and learning languages. Here are some of my favorites in each of the categories:

  • Mamma Mia
  • LaLaLand
  • (Flag) Football
  • Soccer
